Bugfix: Correctly match anchored patterns containing multiple `**`

Exclude and include patterns anchored at the filesystem root and containing
more than one `**` wildcard failed to match paths for which a later `**` had
to match zero directories. For example, the pattern `/srv/**/data/**/*.key`
did not match the path `/srv/app/data/secret.key`, and `/home/**/cache/**`
did not match `/home/user/cache`, even though `**` is documented to match
zero or more directories. As a result, `backup` could include files that an
exclude pattern should have excluded, and `restore` could skip files that an
include pattern should have restored. Restic now matches these patterns
correctly.

